On Saturday 11/9 I met 6 of my friends, all of us former Hooters girls from Towson for a reunion (it had been many years) to celebrate the life of our friend who recently passed.  It was a very special occasion for us.  However the service was horrific.  It took about 20-30 minutes to get a drink, and we had to remind our server what we ordered because at one point she came back to the table and half of us didn't even have a drink and she looked like a deer in headlights - she had zero recollection of us ordering anything.    Then after catching up with one another, we realized an hour plus had passed and our food didn't come out.  Cheese Sticks, wings, buffalo shrimp and crab legs should not take over an hour.  We tried to cancel the food because we had to leave to meet other friends to continue the celebration of life for our friend and miraculously our food came right out.  But the order was missing items and one of the orders just never came out even though we had to remind our server multiple times what was ordered.  BUT DON'T WORRY! Gratuity was added to the check and nothing was discounted for the inconvenience of waiting for so long...  so clearly the server couldn't have cared less about our experience because she knew she was getting paid regardless.  She blamed it on the kitchen being "backed up" even though the restaurant was hardly half full. We would have asked for a manager but after 2 hours we had to leave because our plans had been delayed due to the lack of service.  A table full of former Hooters girls are well aware of ticket times/customer service and looking around the restaurant (basically half empty) and the bar (4 people) it is unacceptable that we had to pay full price for food and drink that we waited a ridiculous amount of time for.  Its unfortunate because we all have fond memories of working for Hooters and don't even want to return because of the awful experience.
